      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Pressure-flow characteristic validation against FDA bench test data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted pressure-flow curves for the centrifugal blood pump were compared against FDA bench measurements across all 5 operating points. Mean absolute error in hydraulic head was 3.2%, within the 5% acceptance threshold established for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/cpb-hemolysis-index-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative hemolysis index validation against in-vitro measurements",
      "description": "Computed relative hemolysis index (RH) values were compared against in-vitro hemolysis measurements from the predicate device test campaign. All 5 operating points yielded RH < 1, consistent with the acceptance criterion. The power-law hemolysis damage model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) reproduced the rank ordering of hemolysis across operating conditions with Spearman rho = 0.94."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/cpb-mesh-convergence",
